verses.text: And this \add is\add* the blessing , wherewith Moses the man of God blessed the children of Israel before his death.

And he said , The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came from Sinai , and rose up from Seir unto them; he shined forth from mount Paran , and he came with ten thousands of saints : from his right hand \add went\add* a fiery law for them.\f + \fr 33.2 \ft a fiery…: Heb. a fire of law\f*
Yea , he loved the people ; all his saints \add are\add* in thy hand : and they sat down at thy feet ; \add every one\add* shall receive of thy words.
Moses commanded us a law , \add even\add* the inheritance of the congregation of Jacob.
And he was king in Jeshurun , when the heads of the people \add and\add* the tribes of Israel were gathered together. \p
¶ Let Reuben live , and not die ; and let \add not\add* his men be few. \p

¶ And this \add is the blessing\add* of Judah : and he said , Hear , \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, the voice of Judah , and bring him unto his people : let his hands be sufficient for him; and be thou an help \add to him\add* from his enemies. \p
¶ And of Levi he said , \add Let\add* thy Thummim and thy Urim \add be\add* with thy holy one , whom thou didst prove at Massah , \add and with\add* whom thou didst strive at the waters of Meribah ;
Who said unto his father and to his mother , I have not seen him; neither did he acknowledge his brethren , nor knew his own children : for they have observed thy word , and kept thy covenant.

They shall teach Jacob thy judgments , and Israel thy law : they shall put incense before thee, and whole burnt sacrifice upon thine altar.\f + \fr 33.10 \ft They shall teach: or, Let them teach\f*\f + \fr 33.10 \ft they shall put: or, let them put\f*\f + \fr 33.10 \ft before…: Heb. at thy nose\f*

Bless , \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, his substance , and accept the work of his hands : smite through the loins of them that rise against him, and of them that hate him, that they rise not again. \p

¶ \add And\add* of Benjamin he said , The beloved of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* shall dwell in safety by him; \add and the \+nd Lord\+nd*\add* shall cover him all the day long, and he shall dwell between his shoulders. \p
¶ And of Joseph he said , Blessed of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add be\add* his land , for the precious things of heaven , for the dew , and for the deep that coucheth beneath ,
And for the precious fruits \add brought forth\add* by the sun , and for the precious things put forth by the moon ,\f + \fr 33.14 \ft put: Heb. thrust\f*\f + \fr 33.14 \ft moon: Heb. moons\f*
And for the chief things of the ancient mountains , and for the precious things of the lasting hills ,

And for the precious things of the earth and fulness thereof, and \add for\add* the good will of him that dwelt in the bush : let \add the blessing\add* come upon the head of Joseph , and upon the top of the head of him \add that was\add* separated from his brethren.

His glory \add is like\add* the firstling of his bullock , and his horns \add are like\add* the horns of unicorns : with them he shall push the people together to the ends of the earth : and they \add are\add* the ten thousands of Ephraim , and they \add are\add* the thousands of Manasseh.\f + \fr 33.17 \ft unicorns: Heb. an unicorn\f* \p
¶ And of Zebulun he said , Rejoice , Zebulun , in thy going out ; and, Issachar , in thy tents.

They shall call the people unto the mountain ; there they shall offer sacrifices of righteousness : for they shall suck \add of\add* the abundance of the seas , and \add of\add* treasures hid in the sand. \p
¶ And of Gad he said , Blessed \add be\add* he that enlargeth Gad : he dwelleth as a lion , and teareth the arm with the crown of the head.

And he provided the first part for himself, because there, \add in\add* a portion of the lawgiver , \add was he\add* seated ; and he came with the heads of the people , he executed the justice of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and his judgments with Israel.\f + \fr 33.21 \ft seated: Heb. cieled\f* \p
¶ And of Dan he said , Dan \add is\add* a lion’s whelp : he shall leap from Bashan. \p
¶ And of Naphtali he said , O Naphtali , satisfied with favour , and full with the blessing of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: possess thou the west and the south. \p
¶ And of Asher he said , \add Let\add* Asher \add be\add* blessed with children ; let him be acceptable to his brethren , and let him dip his foot in oil.
Thy shoes \add shall be\add* iron and brass ; and as thy days , \add so shall\add* thy strength \add be\add*.\f + \fr 33.25 \ft Thy shoes: or, Under thy shoes\f* \p
¶ \add There is\add* none like unto the God of Jeshurun , \add who\add* rideth upon the heaven in thy help , and in his excellency on the sky.
The eternal God \add is thy\add* refuge , and underneath \add are\add* the everlasting arms : and he shall thrust out the enemy from before thee; and shall say , Destroy \add them\add*.
Israel then shall dwell in safety alone : the fountain of Jacob \add shall be\add* upon a land of corn and wine ; also his heavens shall drop down dew.

Happy \add art\add* thou, O Israel : who \add is\add* like unto thee, O people saved by the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, the shield of thy help , and who \add is\add* the sword of thy excellency ! and thine enemies shall be found liars unto thee; and thou shalt tread upon their high places.\f + \fr 33.29 \ft found…: or, subdued\f*
